Arcanys joined the Accelerance Certified Partner Network in 2015. Arcanys is a high quality Accelerance Partner of about 100+ experienced software developers located in Cebu City, Philippines. For more than 5 years, Arcanys has created and developed software for European, Australian, North American startups, mid-sized and Fortune 500 companies.

Run by a team of successful entrepreneurs on-site in the Philippines, Arcanys works to get their client's new products or new ventures on the market as soon as possible. They build teams around startup ideas and dedicate resources to technical teams to help clients find their way fast. Arcanys’ expertise lies in helping companies to create innovative and reliable software solutions in a very short period of time using the latest best-practices and technologies. They focus on Agile / Scrum processes and PHP (Symphony2 mainly), Node.JS, Angular.JS, Python, .NET, JAVA, iOS, Android and cross-platform mobile technologies.

Their focus is delivering value for the money invested, a primary reason they decided to base the company in Cebu, which has been ranked amongst the Top 10 destinations for outsourcing in the world. They are able to draw from a highly educated, nearly native English-speaking talent pool while having some of the lowest labour rates on the planet, coupled with a strong emphasis on inter-cultural training and better collaborations with people from Western cultures. In addition, they have certified Scrum Masters to keep the project and the teams perfectly aligned. They can onboard teams quickly, because they maintain a pool of talented programmers that are ready to be deployed as needed.

ArkusNexus joined the ACE Partner Network in 2015. ArkusNexus is a San Diego, California-based technology company with development offices in Tijuana, Mexico.

Founded in 2004, the company's nearshore software development solutions provide an outstanding option for clients looking for a convenient timezone, culture match to the United States, and close location to the United States. Located only 20 miles from Downtown San Diego, ArkusNexus makes it easy for clients to have frequent face-to-face meetings with their software development team.

AkrusNexus maintains a team of 100+ developers.

BairesDev is a technology services company that employs the Top 1% Talent and specializes in Software Development, Software Outsourcing, Testing, Maintenance & IT Staff Augmentation solutions. Headquartered in San Francisco (CA), BairesDev offers a cost-effective blended model making use of its Development Centers in Latin America.

Having executed more than 850 projects and receiving more than 40,000 new job applicants per year, BairesDev takes advantage of its ability to employ only the Top 1% talent of the IT market to build comprehensive and innovative products for its clients. Companies like Google, Panasonic, and Sirius XM along with many successful startups trust BairesDev to help them create and maintain their products and expand their Software Engineering teams.

Belatrix Software is a leading company in the high-quality, innovative software product development industry. The firm works every day to become the most innovative partner for companies who believe that customized software solutions can make the difference. Belatrix makes ideas come to life.

With over 10 years of experience in various Agile methodologies in both development and testing, we'll be sure to tailor your ideas into world-class software products. All individuals at Belatrix are trained in Agile, and more than 30% of employees are Certified Scrum Masters. The company invests heavily in training, achieving an impressive average of 120 annual hours per individual. The training covers technical skills, management, languages and more.

Belatrix Software helps clients achieve the full impact of their R&D capabilities developing innovative software, quality assurance, testing and mobile solutions. These solutions enable clients to generate best-in-class software products, decrease time to market, and gain competitive edge. The company's collaborative approach delivers high quality software products using multiple technologies and platforms such as mobile, user experience (UX), big data, open source and more.

Belatrix's offices are located in Mendoza and Buenos Aires in Argentina, Bogotá in Colombia, and Lima, Perú. These locations enable Belatrix to offer clients the benefits of nearshore - offering simplified day-to-day management, efficient communication, cultural alignment, easy travelling and lower total cost of engagement. Clients include both established Fortune level and emerging, venture-backed firms, such as Disney, Adobe, SiriusXM, mFoundry, FIS and Chatham Financial.

Codics is a relatively new, 2013 Partner of Accelerance.

We took considerable time in vetting and selecting Codics (FKA BigBek), and their combination of in-demand capabilities, location, pricepoint, US corporate and client presence and demonstrated management expertise and philosophy have given us the solid, reasoned confidence to recommend them strongly when the appropriate match exists.

Three of Codics areas of unique, experienced capabilities are: Using technology in education - iPad, iPhone, Online classrooms; Telecom - Sip calls, Asterisk Server, Voice compression Codecs and E-Commerce - Magento, E-commerce security, payment mechanics. Technologies they have experience or excel in include: Drupal, Third party system development (ERP/CRM), Dotnetnuke, Android, iOS, Python/Django, HTML5/CSS#/JQuery, Java, Joomla, Magento, .Net, Oracle ATG, Business Suites and RDBMS, PhP/Mysql, and website design.

Given the company size and industry experience, Codics is ideal for relationships from 2-10 resources.

Brain Station-23 is a 100 person software development company that specializes in enterprise and startup web and mobile application development. Started in 2006, the company has clients throughout the United States, Canada, UK, Denmark, and the Netherlands.

The company is located in Dhaka, Bangladesh. India's neighbour to the East, Bangladesh has an abundance of talented people, yet only a few large outsourcing companies, which has allowed Brain Station-23 to build a highly talented team of 100+ people.

Brain Station-23 has built a competitive edge through its ability to recruit, train, and retain talent. The company has received multiple awards recognizing them as a top outsourcing company - an honor that has helped the company attract more talented developers.

Brain Station-23 follows scrum and Kanban processes for project management, and has multiple CSM and PMP certifications for best management practices. Currently, Brain Station-23 is working on projects that span ASP.net, MVC, Node.js, Java, Angular.ks, Android, iPhone, and MEAN stacks, as well as database projects that use MS Sql, Oracle, MySql, MongoDB, RavenDB, and CouchDB. The company offers clients the ability to hire 2 to 10 people on either an hourly or monthly engagement basis.

An Accelerance Partner since 2015, Bulpros is one of the leading IT services and solution providers in Southeastern Europe. The company is located in Sofia, Bulgaria and has additional offices in the United States, Germany and Poland. Bulpros boasts a team of over 400 permanent employees, and along with strategic partners, they are part of a network of more than 1000 IT-experts and consultants.

Bulpros supports customers in various industries and provides the entire spectrum of IT lifecycle services – software development in all core technologies (Microsoft, Java, Open Source, Embedded), design and development of web and mobile solutions and applications, IT Infrastructure services and Cloud services. To support the operations of the clients' IT systems, Bulpros provides a range of customer services, including helpdesk, application and infrastructure technical support, content and data services as well as telesales and telemarketing services.

The company has established successful customer and partner relations with Fortune 500 IT companies such as Cisco, Microsoft, IBM, Unisys, VMware, Siemens, and T-Systems. Bulpros is a co-founder of the Bulgarian Outsourcing Association and a member of the American Chamber of Commerce and the German Outsourcing Association. The company has successfully completed over 150 outsourcing projects and developed two of its own products – Staffico, a cloud solution for HR agencies and recruitment teams; and Jabborate, which adds real-time communications to the clients' web systems, integrating them with Cisco Unified Communications and WebEx.

Bulpros is experienced in a range of delivery methodologies and processes for software development – in classical application lifecycle management models as well as agile Scrum based development. Their software development resources are continuously certified and trained in state-of-the-art technological advancements. Furthermore, with the proper mix of technical expertise in the latest technologies, project management skills and application of industry standards such as ISO 9001, ISO 27001 and ITIL, they are able to deliver solutions with excellent quality in the area of operations and infrastructure support. Their IT Infrastructure and Application Management Services offer reliable ITIL-compliant support for complex environments.

Their access to a large network of IT professionals and skilled experts further guarantees the timely delivery of services. They rely on dedicated IT recruitment teams and a substantial database of preselected resources for new hiring.

CINQ Technologies is a software services company based in Curitiba, Brazil and while they have historically been a Brazilian success story, they have more recently turned their services to outside markets due to more advantageous pricing arbitrage. Today, CINQ is growing fastest primarily in foreign markets such as the US and Europe.

Started in 1992, CINQ is certified in CMMI Level 3 and ISO 9001 to assure the quality of the software projects while being dedicated practitioners of Scrum development. CINQ has approximately 250-300 software developers centralized in their development campus in Curitiba. Commitment, innovation and quality are part of the company's DNA and these words form the brand: CINQ. Besides the technical competence, the use of the BPM, latest technologies and methodologies like Agile Scrum, we care that our customers have the best experience in working together with CINQ.

Since 2011, CINQ is a consistent “Best Places to Work” award recipient in Brazil. They develop across a broad set of technologies with the most common areas being .Net/C#, Java, Mobile (Native iOS, Android), Sharepoint, BI, Javascript, LAMP, Ruby, C++.

Comtrade has been an Accelerance Certified and Assessed Partner since 2015. They have over 20 years of experience working from Slovenia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia, and Montenegro, serving companies around the world with a high concentration in and around Western Europe. They are the largest services organization in their region.

Comtrade is divided into three key solutions areas: Digital Services, which is primarily custom software development; Software, which is internally built and owned and reusable for sale and for clients efforts, and Gaming.

Moreover, Comtrade has special, deep expertise in several industry verticals including FinTech, Logistics, Medical, High-tech Energy and e-learning, Public and Telco.

There are several excellent reasons and opportunities to select this partner. If you feel your team is going to scale over time and you need a dedicated software development provider that not only has an excellent reputation in coding quality, but also in consultative vertical and application type experience, then Comtrade is an excellent option.

Their combination of experience, depth, western client exposure, cultural alignment, and cost-effectiveness are all good reasons to choose Comtrade. Accelerance Assessment Photos: https://goo.gl/photos/G51rPgeBiiG3yutL8

Cyber Group, an Accelerance Partner since 2013, provides comprehensive software architecture, development and enterprise integration to mid to large size companies.

Launched in 1998, Cyber Group’s founders have strong engineering (software and hardware design) backgrounds from organizations like Texas Instruments and Accenture. Today, the company has 115+ employees between Dallas, Texas and New Delhi, India. While the company is able to scale resources to accommodate sizeable teams of 15 or more, clients most commonly rely upon Cyber Group for long term engagements with an average team size of 5. Cyber Group leverages several US offices to provide customers a local direct contact and to minimize culture barriers.

Ebryx is a US and Pakistan based engineering consultancy firm offering systems engineering and software development services in telecom, security and web applications. Management and ownership comes by way of Stanford University with extensive US and Silicon Valley experience.

Ebryx was assessed and joined the Accelerance partner network community in 2014. We were in the area so we paid them another visit in 2017, and still loved what we saw. They made a point of focus to increase their depth in cybersecurity services, which is now their strongest domain. Ebryx is providing cybersecurity product engineering services to startups as well as established companies. They have now extended this to enterprise and SMB security consultancy services and 24x7 security monitoring services. Ebryx has also increased their knowledge base in data science, machine learning, embedded systems, and blockchain based apps.

Hexacta boasts an impressive 7 offices, located in: Reston, Virginia; Sao Paulo, Brazil; Montevideo, Uruguay; as well as Buenos Aires, Parana, La Plata, and Bahia Blanca, Argentina. An Accelerance partner since 2015 with 15+ years of experience to their name, Hexacta is a leading Latin American consulting and software development company known for their employees’ quality, the excellence of their methodology, and their experience in new technologies.

Hexacta is considered a center of technological excellence. Over the years they have won several awards in recognition for their work. In 2009 they were named the best IT Company in Argentina by the Chamber of Software and IT Services in Argentina (an award that was delivered by the President of Argentina herself). In 2013 they were again recognized for their outstanding business trajectory (lifelong achievement award). Hexacta is a pioneer in the region in the adoption and development of new technologies and methodologies. In 2003 they were the first Argentinean company (and one of the first in Latin America) to embrace the CMM model and be assessed at CMM level 3. In 2005 they were assessed at CMM level 4. More recently, they have become leaders in Agile development. They are a Registered Education Provider of the Scrum Alliance and the only company in Argentina authorized to provide Scrum and Agile-related training and courses leading to the Certified Scrum Developer credentials.

Hexacta prides themselves on offering world-class services through agile or traditional methodologies by relying on the most talented pool of engineers in the region. This, in conjunction with their long list of credentials, makes Hexacta a great fit for clients all the way from the start-up level to large multi-nationals.

HTEC has been an Accelerance fully vetted partner since 2015. They is a European private R&D center, founded in 2008, with development centers in Serbia (Belgrade and Nis) and rep offices in Sweden (Malmo) and USA (San Francisco). With over thirty years experience in providing payment and loyalty solutions to the retail and petroleum industry, the extensive knowledge HTEC has accumulated through their software products ensure they deliver integrated, sophisticated business IT solutions.

HTEC has diversified skillsets across multiple teams

  • * Embedded Engineering (DSP, Custom electronics, Low level software, Firmware)
  • * Hardware development and verification
  • * Software Development (Application level programming, Desktop, Web and Mobile apps)

Since 2008, HTEC has been providing development services for large corporate customers and for the set of smaller companies and startups mostly from USA and EU, and they have built a reputation as a reliable and high quality development partner.

An Accelerance Certified and On-site Assessed Partner since 2015, Incrys is based in Bucharest, Romania, with offices in Rotterdam and London. The company provides Dedicated Development Teams, Software Development, IT&C Infrastructure, and Consulting Services for clients in Western Europe, USA and Canada.

Started in 2000 as a family-owned-and-managed business, Incrys has evolved into a leading firm that for 4 years in a row placed in the ‘Deloitte Technology CEE Fast 50’ and ‘EMEA Fast 500’. Much of this success is due to their active focus on people. They constantly invest in their employees’ training, professional development, and general work-related wellbeing. Their people-oriented approach secures their place as trusted partner and insures their clients can always find the appropriate resources to empower their business.

Accelerance onsite assessment photos

Incrys has the ability to come in at any stage of idea development and start creating software based on their client’s current needs and future requirements. Building from the ground up, Incrys puts heavy focus on creating a development plan to keep their clients in close communication. Incrys delivers ERP, CRM, Business Intelligence, Business Analytics and Optimization, as well as insuring adaptive, corrective, preventive, and perfective software maintenance. Incrys puts their applications goes through a rigorous testing process to assure quality. They are extremely well versed in a range of technologies, including Java, PHP, Cobol, OBI, IBM D2, Ab Initio, Unix, CSS, C++, HTML, XML, and many more. They back this up with over 40 technological certifications.

Ingenuity has been an Accelerance Partner since 2014.

Primarily focused on web development using Python/Django and mobile applications development on iOS, they've done a lot of exciting work for both start-ups and established firms in: healthcare, advertising, mapping, cloud-hosting, education, games, mobile apps, file-sharing, video-streaming, shopping, non-profit organizations, and more.

Ingenuity is close to 100 engineers located in Davao City, in the south, and the third largest city in the Philippines (about 2.5mm) known for better education, lower prices, and lower turnover than Manila.

Intellias is a challenge-driven software engineering company, based in Ukraine (Kyiv, Lviv, Odesa) and locally represented in Berlin.

Since 2002 they have been helping leading technology companies from EU and North America to create their software products by building and operating world-class engineering teams in Eastern Europe for them. Intellias created a comprehensive system of tools and practices to ensure a quick ramp-up, perfect culture match, high productivity and great quality of the output for our teams.

In 2017 Intellias received a recognition from Inc 5000 as one of the fastest growing privately held companies in Europe and has been nominated to GSA UK Awards 2017. Highly rated by its customers and employees, it has been awarded a status of Lviv's top IT employer since 2010 (DOU.ua) and is now one of Ukraine's top 5 midsize IT employers; also KPMG highlighted Intellias as one of the top ITO-BPO providers in Lviv.

Due to a fully-fledged presence in the most beneficial hiring markets and biggest IT hubs, Intellias has access to 70,000 engineers in Ukraine. This vast access to resources strengthened by Intellias' prominent position in the labor market is a perfect match for clients that would like to quickly scale outside of their local recruitment market, explore locations currently untapped by global players or find narrow profiled specialists.

iTransition has been an Accelerance Assessed Partner since 2006! The latest Onsite Assessment was performed March 2013.

iTransition specializes in Java, .Net and Testing with other core capabilities in Mobile, Drupal, LAMP, Open Source CMS, Sharepoint, MS Dynamics CRM, Joomla, Magento, HTML5, PHP, Linux/C++, Ruby and in financial services. Itransition provides advanced full lifecycle testing and quality assurance services to software product companies and enterprises.

The service offering includes: - QA Consulting - QA Audit - Functional testing - Test automation - Mobile testing - Web app testing - Performance testing - Security testing - Localization and internationalization testing - Pre-certification product testing (including PCI DSS certification) -Documentation services.

Located in beautiful Minsk, Belarus with US offices in Austin, TX, iTransition employs about 850 developers with excellent English skills throughout the organization. Rates are very globally competitive. iTransition is best for clients who need between 4-100 resources.

Kambda is a fast-growing Accelerance Partner led by an all-star project manager, architect and developer with long, experienced ties to the Accelerance team.

The company’s HQ and leadership team are in San José, Costa Rica but its development team is spread throughout Latin America. Kambda’s leadership team is made up of a very experienced CTO & Founder with a Master’s degree in computer engineering and a CEO that has a strong financial and administrative background and an MBA. Kambda has a unique hiring and freelance model that gives them the ability to bring new team members on board in a short period of time and at a cost savings to traditional software service factories. Even though Costa Rican prices are relatively high in Latin America, Kambda’s distributed structure allows it to charge lower competitive rates.

Kambda’s experience has mainly focused on technologies such as native and cross-platform mobile development, Ruby on Rails, PHP, Python, NodeJS, Java, .Net, Sharepoint, Joomla, Drupal, Wordpress, HTML5, AngularJS, Bootstrap and CSS3. They also have strong growth in mobile development. Due to their business model, they are able to get bring in an expert in any technology clients may need for a software development project, while they supervise the successful completion of the project and keep clients informed from the company’s HQ in San José.

KMS Technology joined the Accelerance Expert Network in 2014, but has been involved with Accelerance since 2012.

With 10+ years of experience under their belt operating offices in Atlanta, Georgia; San Francisco, California; and Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam; KMS is well-positioned as a reliable global partner. KMS prides itself on helping companies with software solutions custom built from the ground up.

KMS is a premium provider in Java, .NET, and mobile app development, and has built a world-class practice in Software Testing. The company currently has a team of 500, and is targeting near-term growth to 1,000. KMS is a perfect vendor for companies generating up to $250 million in revenue that are seeking a long term, dedicated team engagement model. KMS's operating model demands that its entire team in Vietnam have strong communication and consulting skills in order to directly communicate with clients.

KMS puts a huge focus on providing clients with a customer centric and solutions-oriented approach while creating a scalable product that allows their client to be flexible and adapt quickly to changing demands. KMS is a desirable choice for a wide variety of clients.

Nexient is a leader in the Agile, domestic IT services and outsourcing market. Through its Onshore Development Centers, the company provides its clients with a uniquely cost-efficient and responsive IT service delivery model.

Leveraging about 500 development staff in Michigan and Indiana, they work with some of the biggest and most technologically advanced enterprises to help them design, develop, test and implement technology products and applications that run critical business functions.

Nexient is making significant investments in long-term IT workforce development to drive the next generation of American technology leadership.

Omnisource Technologies joined the ACE Partner Network in 2014. Started in 2006, the company has two development offices in Romania, a strategic business development office in New York and more than 40 full time professionals.

Three areas of unique, experienced capabilities where Omnisource Technologies excel are (1) the Healthcare/EMR market, (2) the Online Entertainment market, and (3) with ISV's. Technologies they have experience or excel in include: Agile, Android, Business Intel, DotNetNuke, Drupal, Flash / Flex, HTML5 / CSS3 / Jquery, iOS, Java, Joomla, Magento, Microsoft.NET, Mobile Apps, PhoneGap, PHP & MySQL, Sencha, Software Testing, SugarCRM, Web Design, Windows Phone 8, and Wordpress.

With a team of 50 developers (growing in near term to 100), Omnisource looks to build and operate long-term remote dedicated teams for its clients with team sizes ranging from 3 to 15+.

Oxagile is a leading-edge provider of custom application development services with a strong focus on web and mobile. Their services cover all your software development needs — including prototyping, building, testing, maintenance and support.

Headquartered in the US, the company employs over 200 tech engineers in its state-of-the-art offshore development center in Minsk, the capital of Belarus, Eastern Europe.

Belarus is an exceptional outsourcing destination with a robust education system. The country’s top three technical universities are conveniently located in Minsk as well. Each year, they produce thousands of highly-qualified professionals with a B.S. or M.S. degree in Computer Science. The availability of great IT talent enables Oxagile to quickly ramp up the resources as projects demand.

Oxagile utilizes an agile, low-risk software development approach that emphasizes communication, measurable results, and timely delivery. The Company has been in the outsourcing market for over a decade, and has accumulated thousands of man-years of hands-on experience in a wide array of technologies, vertical industries, and business domains. They have particular expertise in areas such as VoD and Online Video, Real Time Communication, Education and e-Learning, e-Commerce, Finance, and Entertainment.

From a technology perspective, Oxagile strives to maintain the highest level of competence across the modern web and mobile tech stack. Their engineers are proficient in Java, .NET, PHP, HTML5 and CSS3, as well as modern JavaScript frameworks such as Angular, Backbone, Knockout, Node.js, and Meteor.js. They also employ a team specializing in mobile and cross-platform technologies and OSs, including Android, iOS, PhoneGap, Xamarin, and more.

Oxagile is also a Microsoft Gold Competency Partner for Application Development, which reinforces their expertise in the .NET stack.

For three years in a row, Oxagile has been named to the authoritative IAOP Global Outsourcing 100® list of the best outsourcing companies in the world. The company also made the prestigious Inc. 5000 list of the fastest-growing private companies in the United States — in 2013 and 2014.

They have worked with both small and midsize businesses, as well as some of the world’s best-known brands like Google, Discovery Communications, and Vodafone.

ProximityCR is the oldest Accelerance Partner in their network, with approximately 100 expert Agile software Engineers in Costa Rica and a small operation of about 15 engineers in Argentina.

They have been helping clients in the US and Canada since 2004, in multiple industries and verticals, working startups, small and mid-sized companies, and fortune 500 enterprises. All these years of experience has allowed them to create unique services that pull together 3 main factors:

1- A deep technical expertise in the services they provide and the technologies they use.

2- A highly strong expertise in the delivery model, being the experts on a meaningful and proven Nearshore Agile approach, with

3- The best talent available, English-speaking, continuously trained, outspoken and collaborative, working from beautiful Costa Rica!

Whether you need to improve the performance, functionality or effectiveness of your existing applications, build a new solution from scratch, or port your applications and functionality to mobile devices, they have the expertise to help you.

From Web Applications to Service Oriented Architecture – SOA-, Software as a Service – SaaS – Cloud computing to native and cross platform Mobile Development, they have developed expertise and proprietary tools that can help you to speed up the development process, increasing standardization, quality and security, and reducing the time to market, while clients recieve easy-to-maintain applications that are portable, scalable and feature a great user interface.

Quality Assurance services is another of their core specialties, involving functional, automated performance and security testing, both for web and mobile.

They have three delivery centers in San Jose, Costa Rica, each of them specialized on a particular set of technologies, at a deep level:

1- Microsoft Dot Net and Site Core

2- Open Source technologies such as PHP, PHP, Ruby on Rails, NodeJS, Java, MAGENTO, Joomla, Drupal, Wordpress, HTML5, AngularJS, Bootstrap, CSS3, etc.

3- Native and cross platform Mobile (iOS and Android)

Technologies and methodologies are important and useful things when properly used. Proximity has developed the expertise to master these factors over the years, but they believe that software development in general, and Nearshore Outsourcing more specifically, is a matter of people dealing with people, and that is why they focus their attention on creating an exceptional experience with clients.

PSL has been a standout Accelerance Partner for over 5 years, managing some of our biggest clients and most challenging projects. Their CMMi Level 5 accreditation coupled with their SCRUM expertise makes them an agile partner that can predictably deliver quality services. In addition, their combination of location, tremendous communication skills and size and breadth of capabilities make them a compelling option for ISV startups and larger company back office development alike.

With approximately 550 employees and over 30 years of experience, they consider themselves large enough to matter, but small enough to care. This means that all their clients have direct access to their c-level executives, and it means as well that all their clients are able to have services tailored to their specific needs – whether this be adjustments in the technology being used, or specific changes in the methodology used to deploy services.

Although Colombia isn’t the first place people think about for software development, the country has become extremely stable and politically aligned with the US in recent years, and their excellent infrastructure and relatively underutilized deep talent pool makes Colombia a new, hot near shore destination for the next decade to come at least!

Quadrant 4 has been an Accelerance Partner since 2011. They have proven practices for creating large mission-critical enterprise applications using .NET, Java and QA principally. In addition, they have practices to implement SAP and Oracle Applications with both technology consulting and on-going support.

A key hallmark of this preferred partner is their ability to put experts at the client site to both elicit and document requirements and then interact with the development team in Chennai or Hyderabad throughout implementation. They have senior software engineers and business analysts who have worked in the U.S. and other western countries and have led many such client engagements using this onsite / offshore model.

Quadrant 4 is larger than most Accelerance Partners (about 700) so the can scale easily but they are small enough to make every client a top priority.

Santex, an Accelerance Partner since 2015, is based in San Diego, California with two development centers in Córdoba, Argentina and Lima, Peru. Founded in 1999, the company has over fifteen years of experience providing software development services to companies across the US, from startups to Fortune 100 companies, including Wal-Mart, Coca-Cola, Accenture, Macy’s, ESPN, Sirius Satellite Radio, Coldwell Banker, and the US Department of Transportation.

The Santex distinguishes themselves through their commitment to their work, their flexibility, and their professionalism – commitments that are evident in all interactions with their team.

Santex provides fully integrated software solutions that span through all the phases of the development cycle, from requirements analysis and architecture to the programming, testing and implementation of the software product. The Company provides specific skills, knowledge and experience through technology hubs which include E-commerce, Mobility, Integration, Content Delivery, IT Services, Big Data, and Cloud Computing. They employ a team of 170+ technology experts who possess the highest seniority in the market (80% plus are senior level), including Architects, Developers, Functional Analysts, Project Managers, SCRUM Masters, UI and UX experts, and others.

Santex is very accommodating, and team members will travel to their clients when required. It is this willingness to be onsite that helps develop a lasting relationship while demonstrating the company’s commitment to serving the client’s needs.

An Accelerance Certified Assessed Partner since 2015, ScaleFocus is a leading European software company, holding a number of national and international awards, with offices in four European cities: Sofia, London, Munich and Plovdiv. Accelerance visited Scalefocus in 2015 on an assessment trip and was highly impressed with both the current structure and processes but also with the company’s ambitious plans for growth and improvement.

In the last three years, Scalefocus has successfully delivered over 70 projects to customers in 14 countries, across Europe, North America and Asia. At the beginning of 2017, the company had built a team of over 260 specialists and continues to grow dynamically. The main customers of ScaleFocus are enterprises in the IT, telecom, financial and logistics sectors.

The company offers services in the following major domains:

  • Software solutions’ development and integration
  • Data, Information and Processes management; eCommerce; Mobile; Portals
  • Managed services and end-to-end solutions implementation
  • quality engineering and system audits

ScaleFocus is known for its expertise in the newest and most innovative niche technologies. The company won the trust of partners like IBM, Microsoft, TIBCO, VMware, Citrix, Veeam, Oracle, Teradata and more. ScaleFocus has also implemented world-class internal processes and delivery practices, standardized on ISO 9001 for Quality Management, ISO 20000 for Managed Services and ISO 27000 for Information Security.

The experts within the company are recognized for their technical excellence, industry expertise and diverse backgrounds. They are passionate and focused. They understand the meaning of being customer-centric and believe in what they do.

ScaleFocus’ sophisticated technical capabilities enable companies of any size to focus on core competencies and achieve sustainable business growth in a lean, agile and cost-effective way.

Scalefocus Assessment Trip Photos

Scio has been an Accelerance Partner since 2010.

Scio specializes in web, cloud and mobile apps, primarily using a Microsoft stack of technologies. Accelerance visited Scio in 2011 and we were very impressed with their infrastructure, English-speaking talent and depth of development acumen.

Scio has ownership and management located in Austin, TX.

Located in Belarus’ Tech-centric capital city of Minsk, Softteco is located in the geographic center of Europe with 4-5 hours’ work overlap with the US East Coast. Softteco has an excellent level of English fluency.

With about 60 developers, Softteco is perfect for of between 2-15 developers.

TektonLabs has been an Accelerance Assessed Partner since 2012. Accelerance performed an onsite Assessment in 2012, 2014 and 2016! They specialize in Java, .Net, and Testing with other core capabilities in Sharepoint, all mobile platforms, Flash/flex, website design, Drupal, Magento, Joomla, HTML5, PHP, Ruby, Python/Django, dotnetnuke. Tekton has served more than 25 Accelerance clients over the past 5 years.
